{"name": "opentelemetry-instrumentation-alephalpha", "metadata": {"name": "opentelemetry-instrumentation-alephalpha", "version": "0.33.12", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "https://github.com/traceloop/openllmetry/tree/main/packages/opentelemetry-instrumentation-alephalpha", "license": "Apache-2.0", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["opentelemetry-api", "opentelemetry-instrumentation", "opentelemetry-semantic-conventions", "opentelemetry-semantic-conventions-ai"], "summary": "OpenTelemetry Aleph Alpha instrumentation", "upload_time": 1731529632}, "documentation": ["# OpenTelemetry Aleph Alpha Instrumentation\n\n<a href=\"https://pypi.org/project/opentelemetry-instrumentation-alephalpha/\">\n    <img src=\"https://badge.fury.io/py/opentelemetry-instrumentation-alephalpha.svg\">\n</a>\n\nThis library allows tracing calls to any of Aleph Alpha's endpoints sent with the official [Aleph Alpha Client](https://github.com/Aleph-Alpha/aleph-alpha-client).\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install opentelemetry-instrumentation-alephalpha\n```\n\n## Example usage\n\n```python\nfrom opentelemetry.instrumentation.alephalpha import AlephAlphaInstrumentor\n\nAlephAlphaInstrumentor().instrument()\n```\n\n## Privacy\n\n**By default, this instrumentation logs prompts, completions, and embeddings to span attributes**. This gives you a clear visibility into how your LLM application is working, and can make it easy to debug and evaluate the quality of the outputs.\n\nHowever, you may want to disable this logging for privacy reasons, as they may contain highly sensitive data from your users. You may also simply want to reduce the size of your traces.\n\nTo disable logging, set the `TRACELOOP_TRACE_CONTENT` environment variable to `false`.\n\n```bash\nTRACELOOP_TRACE_CONTENT=false\n```\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.alephalpha.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.alephalpha.utils.dont_throw", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["A decorator that wraps the passed in function and logs exceptions instead of throwing them.\n\n@param func: The function to wrap\n@return: The wrapper function"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.alephalpha.version", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.alephalpha.version.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.alephalpha.config", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.alephalpha.config.Config", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.alephalpha.config.Config.exception_logger", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.alephalpha", "documentation": ["OpenTelemetry Aleph Alpha instrumentation"], "functions": [{"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.alephalpha.should_send_prompts", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.alephalpha._set_span_attribute", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "span", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.alephalpha._set_input_attributes", "asynchronous": false, "pa